# Runtime Source Rules

- `src/game.js` is the coordinator. Avoid dumping new feature logic there if an existing feature module owns the behavior.
- Keep rules/data in `src/core/*.js`, `src/data/*.js`, and `src/features/*.js`; keep drawing in `src/ui/render.js`.
- Preserve the project’s plain-object, helper-first style.
- When changing content tables, watch for downstream balance and selector/test assumptions.
- When changing player progression, objectives, contracts, or telemetry, check whether tests or harness scripts need updates.
